Personal Details

 I am an assistant professor in Department of Computer Science 
at New Jersey Institute of Technology (NJIT), USA. 

Check new website here.


Research interests: Databases, security, privacy, and IoT.




 

    Students interested to work with me can see this.  




I was a Post-Doctoral Fellow 
in Department of Computer Science 
at the University of California, Irvine, USA, working in the research group of 
 Prof. Sharad Mehrotra.





I have completed my Ph.D. in 
 Computer Science  at Ben-Gurion University of the Negev, 
Beersheva, 
Israel.  
I am blessed to become an academic son of Prof. Shlomi Dolev 
and to work with  
Prof. Jeffrey Ullman --- a Turing Award winner --- during my Ph.D. and Post-Doc . 



Email: 
shantanu.sharma[AT]njit[DOT]edu
					



